    {
      "role": "user",
      "content": "but it's not just \"feeling\" like a failure. it's the reality. i look at them and i just see how much weight i'm putting on them. i see the stress in their faces because of my mistakes. it's like... if i was gone, the weight would just lift. they could breathe again without me constantly making things harder for them. it feels like the only selfless thing left to do is to stop being the problem.",
